# create train test sets

set.seed(25)

uc_train = subset(uc, split == TRUE)
uc_test = subset(uc, split == FALSE)
lm3 <- lm(price~., data = uc_train) #model
pred3 = predict(lm3, uc_test[,1:11])
sse3 = sum((uc_test[,12]-pred3)^2)
rmse3 = sqrt(sse3 / nrow(uc_test))

## [1] 5627.963
# 10-fold cross validation
# randomly shuffle the data
uc_kfold = uc[sample(nrow(uc)),]
# create 10 equally size folds
folds <- cut(seq(1, nrow(uc_kfold)), breaks = 10, labels = F)
# perform 10 fold cross validation
rmse_list4 = c()
for (i in 1:10){
  testIndexes4 <- which(folds==i, arr.ind = T)
  testData4 <- uc_kfold[testIndexes4, ]
  trainData4 <- uc_kfold[-testIndexes4,]
  lm4 = lm(price~., data = trainData4)
  pred4 = predict(lm4, testData4[,1:11])
  sse4 = sum((testData4[,12] - pred4)^2)
  rmse4 = sqrt(sse4 / nrow(testData4))
  rmse_list4 = c(rmse_list4, rmse4)
}

Classification Analysis

# Classification Analysis
# create a new dataframe with a label column, and without the price column
uc_cla = uc
mean_price = mean(uc_cla$price)
uc_cla$label = sign(uc$price - mean_price)
# delete price column
uc_cla$price <- NULL
# replace -1 with 0
uc_cla$label[uc_cla$label == -1] <- 0
uc_cla$label <- as.factor(uc_cla$label)
# train test split
library(caTools)
set.seed(298)
split2 = sample.split(uc_cla$label, SplitRatio = 0.75)
train.cla = subset(uc_cla, split == TRUE)
test.cla = subset(uc_cla, split == FALSE)
# X,y split
cla.trainX = train.cla[,1:11]
cla.trainy = train.cla[,12]
cla.testX = test.cla[,1:11]
cla.testy = test.cla[,12]
# knn model
library(class)
knn.150 = knn(train = train.cla, test = test.cla, k=150, cl=cla.trainy)
knn.200 = knn(train = train.cla, test = test.cla, k=200, cl=cla.trainy)
# calculate the proportion of correct classification
acc.150 = sum(cla.testy == knn.150) / NROW(cla.testy)
acc.200 = sum(cla.testy == knn.200) / NROW(cla.testy)

Tree-based models

# Tree-based models
# 1. random forest model to predict price, 10-folds to output the rmse
library(randomForest)
set.seed(350)
# randomly shuffle the data
uc.rf <- uc[sample(nrow(uc)),]
# create 10 equally size folds
folds <- cut(seq(1,nrow(uc.rf)),breaks=10,labels=FALSE)
# perform 10 fold cross validation
rmse_list = c()
for(i in 1:10){
  # segement your data by fold using the which() function 
  testIndexes <- which(folds==i,arr.ind=TRUE)
  testData <- uc.rf[testIndexes, ]
  trainData <- uc.rf[-testIndexes, ]
  # build model and obtain 10 rmse
  rf = randomForest(price~., data = trainData, ntree=100)
  pred = predict(rf, testData[, 1:11])
  sse = sum((testData[,12] - pred)^2) # sse = rss
  mse = sse / nrow(testData) # divided by n
  rmse = sqrt(mse)
  rmse_list = c(rmse_list, rmse)
}

# estimate rmse
rms_error_rf = mean(rmse_list)
rms_error_rf
## [1] 3391.89

uc.rf <- uc[sample(nrow(uc)),]
# create 10 equally size folds
folds <- cut(seq(1,nrow(uc.rf)),breaks=10,labels=FALSE)
# perform 10 fold cross validation
rmse_list = c()
for(i in 1:10){
  # segement your data by fold using the which() function 
  testIndexes <- which(folds==i,arr.ind=TRUE)
  testData <- uc.rf[testIndexes, ]
  trainData <- uc.rf[-testIndexes, ]
  # build model and obtain 10 rmse
  rf = randomForest(price~milage+year+make+Cyl_Volume+fuel+body_style+drive_type+Highway_MPG+City_MPG+Num_Cyl, data = trainData, ntree=100)
  pred = predict(rf, testData[, 1:11])
  sse = sum((testData[,12] - pred)^2) # sse = rss
  mse = sse / nrow(testData) # divided by n
  rmse = sqrt(mse)
  rmse_list = c(rmse_list, rmse)
}

# estimate rmse
rms_error_rf = mean(rmse_list)
rms_error_rf
